(49, 'admin_page', 'O:8:"stdClass":26:{s:3:"nid";s:2:"49";s:3:"vid";s:2:"49";s:4:"type";s:10:"admin_page";s:6:"status";s:1:"1";s:7:"created";s:10:"1215625110";s:7:"changed";s:10:"1233172544";s:7:"comment";s:1:"0";s:7:"promote";s:1:"0";s:6:"sticky";s:1:"0";s:18:"revision_timestamp";s:10:"1233172544";s:5:"title";s:33:"About Scholars'' Web Sites Project";s:4:"body";s:1690:"<p>Our project is an effort to build the next generation faculty web\r\nsite.  It will have all the features faculty sites have now, built in\r\na more dynamic and customizable way, along with a suite of much more\r\npowerful tools users can choose from that facilitate creating,distributing, and preserving knowledge faster and more efficiently than ever before. </p>\r\n\r\n<p>For example, scholarly papers you upload to your site appear there,\r\nare automatically distributed to public indices (RePec, PubMed, Google\r\nscholar, SSI, polmeth, SSRN, etc.), and are posted on other relevant\r\nHarvard sites (such as IQSS, your academic department, and the Office\r\nof Scholarly Communication); your papers, or their citation\r\ninformation, and can then be downloaded by others in multiple formats\r\nor subscribed to via RSS feeds.  You can use your site to organize\r\nyour work, publish news and announcements, post presentations, and\r\nclass materials, aggregate and post RSS feeds from other sites, and\r\nmaintain contact with students, colleagues and collaborators.  With a\r\nclick you can add many features, such as a secure facility to share\r\nprivate files, messages, todo lists, calendars, data, and\r\ndocumentation with collaborators prior to public distribution;\r\nestablish a dataverse to distribute data or your view of the universe\r\nof data; create your own blog; or add many wigets such as automatic\r\ntranslation, search, and notification. </p>\r\n\r\n<p>Users have total (password-protected) control over the look, feel, and\r\ncontent of their site through an easy WYSIWYG interface.</p>\r\n\r\n