confounding variables. This paper shows that such a conclusion is unduly pessimistic. Because the complete data likelihood under arbitrary patterns of confounding factorizes in a particularly convenient way, it is possible to parameterize this general situation with four easily interpretable parameters. Subjec- tive beliefs regarding these parameters are easily elicited and subjective statements of uncertainty become possible. This paper also develops a novel graphical display called the confounding plot that quickly and efficiently communicates all patterns of confounding that would leave a particular causal inference relatively unchanged.";s:13:"biblio_abst_f";s:0:"";s:16:"biblio_full_text";s:1:"0";s:15:"biblio_keywords";s:0:"";s:10:"biblio_url";s:0:"";s:10:"biblio_doi";s:0:"";s:12:"biblio_issue";s:0:"";s:19:"biblio_type_of_work";s:0:"";s:23:"biblio_accession_number";s:0:"";s:18:"biblio_call_number";s:0:"";s:12:"biblio_notes";s:0:"";s:12:"biblio_coins";s:544:"<span class="Z3988" title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Adc&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fscholar.iq.harvard.edu&amp;rft.title=What+Can+Be+Learned+from+a+Simple+Table%3F+Bayesian+Inference+and+Sensitivity+Analysis+for+Causal+Effects+from+2+x+2+and+2+x+2+x+K+Tables+in+the+Presence+of+Unmeasured+Confounding&amp;rft.date=2008&amp;rft.aulast=Quinn&amp;rft.aufirst=Kevin&amp;rft.pub=Department+of+Government+and+The+Institute+for+Quantitative+Social+Sciences+Harvard+University&amp;rft.place=Cambridge%2C+MA"></span>";s:21:"biblio_research_notes";s:0:"";s:14:"biblio_custom1";s:0:"";s:14:"biblio_custom2";s:0:"";s:14:"biblio_custom3";s:0:"";s:14:"biblio_custom4";s:0:"";s:14:"biblio_custom5";s:0:"";s:14:"biblio_custom6";s:0:"";s:14:"biblio_custom7";s:0:"";s:19:"biblio_auth_address";s:0:"";s:21:"biblio_remote_db_name";s:0:"";s:25:"biblio_remote_db_provider";s:0:"";s:14:"biblio_citekey";s:3:" 40";s:12:"biblio_label";s:0:"";s:18:"biblio_access_date";s:0:"";s:16:"biblio_type_name";s:13:"Working