eeches represent attempts at deception, persuasion, or impression management. This article tests the validity of using public speech data in operational code analysis by comparing the output to the results one gets by analyzing private statements from the same period. The results strongly indicate that one \r\nobtains the same results using either the public or the private data, thus providing tentative conﬁrmation of the validity of using public speeches for assessing the operational codes of leaders.\r\n";s:13:"biblio_abst_f";s:0:"";s:16:"biblio_full_text";s:1:"0";s:15:"biblio_keywords";s:0:"";s:10:"biblio_url";s:0:"";s:10:"biblio_doi";s:0:"";s:12:"biblio_issue";s:1:"4";s:19:"biblio_type_of_work";s:0:"";s:23:"biblio_accession_number";s:0:"";s:18:"biblio_call_number";s:0:"";s:12:"biblio_notes";s:0:"";s:12:"biblio_coins";s:517:"<span class="Z3988" title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Ajournal&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fscholar.iq.harvard.edu&amp;rft.genre=article&amp;rft.atitle=When+Public+Statements+Reveal+Private+Beliefs%3A+Assessing+Operational+Codes+at+a+Distance&amp;rft.title=Political+Psychology&amp;rft.stitle=When+Public+Statements+Reveal+Private+Beliefs&amp;rft.date=9998&amp;rft.volume=30&amp;rft.issue=4&amp;rft.spage=649&amp;rft.epage=661&amp;rft.aulast=Renshon&amp;rft.aufirst=Jonathan"></span>";s:21:"biblio_research_notes";s:0:"";s:14:"biblio_custom1";s:0:"";s:14:"biblio_custom2";s:0:"";s:14:"biblio_custom3";s:0:"";s:14:"biblio_custom4";s:0:"";s:14:"biblio_custom5";s:0:"";s:14:"biblio_custom6";s:0:"";s:14:"biblio_custom7";s:0:"";s:19:"biblio_auth_address";s:0:"";s:21:"biblio_remote_db_name";s:0:"";s:25:"biblio_remote_db_provider";s:0:"";s:14:"biblio_citekey";s:3:"474";s:12:"biblio_label";s:0:"";s:18:"biblio_access_date";s:0:"";s:16:"biblio_type_name";s:15:"Journal Article";s:4:"path";s:92:"renshon/when-public-statements-reveal-private-beliefs-assessing-operational-codes-a-distance";s:9:"og_groups";a:1:{i:0;i:385;}s:14:"og_g